author: The Associated Press
title: Outrage greets likely House speaker's comments that Benghazi panel hurting Clinton campaign
text: Outrage greets likely House speaker's comments that Benghazi panel hurting Clinton campaign John Boehner, Kevin McCarthy Outgoing House Speaker John Boehner (right) of Ohio listens as House Majority Leader Kevin McCarthy of California speaks during a news conference on Capitol Hill in Washington, D.C., on Tuesday, Sept. 29, 2015. McCarthy in a Fox News interview said everyone thought Hillary Clinton was unbeatable in the 2016 presidential race, but the Republicans put together a special committee on Benghazi and caused her poll numbers to drop. (Carolyn Kaster/The Associated Press)
